---
title: Apple Dutch Baby Pancake with Sausage and Maple Syrup
description: A Dutch baby is basically a next level pancake: the batter is poured into a pan, given a few slices of fruit, and baked in the oven until it puffs up like a big shot proudly and self-assuredly sticking out his chest. When you pull this marvel out of the oven, it seems to exclaim, “Look at me! I am big, beautiful, and I put all those silver-dollar-shaped ’cakes to shame.” So treat this Dutch baby with awe and admiration—few breakfasts are deserving of it as this one.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/apple-dutch-baby-pancake-1303cded.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/apple-dutch-baby-pancake-866b28f6.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 50 g
  protein: 20 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 430 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/apple-dutch-baby-pancake-598cc802a2882a4d594e7e52
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve, core, and cut
@apple{2%unit} into ¼-inch-thick slices. Melt half the @cinnamon butter{4%tablespoon} 
in a medium #ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add apples, @brown sugar{1%tablespoon}, 
and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, tossing, until apples are slightly softened, 
~{3-5%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Transfer empty pan to oven to heat. Meanwhile, crack @eggs{2%unit} into a large 
#bowl{}. Pour in @milk{4%ounce}. Whisk vigorously to combine. Add @flour{½%ounce} 
and beat until smooth (there should be no lumps), ~{2%minutes}. Add remaining 
cinnamon butter to pan and let melt in oven. Once melted, ~{1-2%minutes} later, 
remove pan from oven and swirl to coat surface in butter.

Add half the apple slices to pan in a single layer. Pour batter over apple slices. 
Return pan to oven and bake until batter is puffy and golden brown, 
~{20%minutes}.

> TIP: Resist the temptation to peek. If you don't keep the oven door closed, 
> you may lose the heat needed to make the pancake rise.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in another medium pan over medium-high 
heat. Add @breakfast sausage{4%ounce} and cook, turning occasionally, until browned 
and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Peel @orange{1%unit}, removing as much white pith as possible. Cut into wedges.

> TIP: If you're feeling fancy, try supreming the orange: use a small knife to cut 
> away the peel and pith, then cut out wedges from the flesh, inserting the knife 
> along the sides of the membranes and working over a bowl to catch the wedges 
> and any juice.

Once Dutch baby is done baking, cut into slices and divide between plates. Top 
with orange and remaining apple slices. Drizzle with @maple syrup{1%ounce}. Serve 
with sausages on the side.